  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Supporting artists through 1980 UNESCO Recommendation concerning Status of the Artist as well as 2005Convention</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNESCO 1980 Recommendation concerning the Status of the Artist is little known in the sub-region including India and Sri Lanka. New Delhi Culture is planning to intensify its efforts to raise awareness of it to encourage the artists of the sub-region to be mobilised to improve their precarious status. on the other hand, New Delhi Culture is planning to produce three national languages version of the Legal Handbook for Artists (Visual Arts) which was released in 2020 August. National versions of the Legal Handbook (Three major local languages: Hindi, Bengali and Marathi) will reach out to a much larger numbers of artists, hence greatly contribute to defend their own right in various complex issues related to their artistic works.</narrative>
  </description>
